args: Where is the prince of the Halidom?!
Greetings, Elder of the northeast forest.\nWhat do you need with me?
What do I NEED? For you to hand\nover the thief hiding away in this\ncastle, that's what!
Please, calm down. I don't follow.
I speak of the nurse of the Halidom! She\npicked one of our prized camirela herbs!
You can't mean Aeleen, can you?
Yes? I'm Aeleen. Do you need some—
THIEF! You would dare come and steal\nthe camirela from our woods?!
What?! What are you talking about?
Elder! What evidence have you for this\nallegation?
Oh, you want evidence? I have plenty!\nI saw a human figure fleeing the woods!
And once the figure had escaped, I found\nnaught but a void where the camirela once\ngrew. Oh, how lamentable!
But all you saw was a figure, yes? That's\nhardly decisive proof that Aeleen did it...
I didn't say I was finished, boy. I also\nwent and inquired among the people\nof the village about the culprit.
That's when I heard a story about a person\nwho was using the herb in medicinal\ncompounds. And it was YOU!
I-I mean, it's true that I heal using the\ncamirela, but I got it from Sylas...

Sir, you labor under a misunderstanding.
I took the camirela I cultivated in the
village, produced more at the Halidom,
and gave some to her.
Is covering for her like that not proof that\nyou yourself were complicit in her larceny?
None save the sylvans know where the\ncamirela grows. How shameful of you\nto abet these humans!
Hey, okay, now you're taking this too far!
It's the truth. Ever since he started\nconsorting with humans, this kind of \nthing—
Forgive me for intruding on this matter.\nI am Isaac, a guardian of the holy land\nof Initio.
Elder, with due respect, Aeleen is not the\ntype to thoughtlessly pilfer something so\nimportant to the sylvans.
To determine guilt without definitive proof,\nwithout listening to your brethren...we of\nthe forest should know better than that.
Grrr! You speak beyond your station, young\nman. What does a stranger like you know?!
I know that to tread upon our great Mother\nNature is an offense of the highest order.\nThus...
I will apprehend any villain who would\nprofane Her and Her myriad bounties.
I'm so sorry to rope you into this, Isaac.
Worry not. Your demonstrable respect for\nnature has convinced me of your innocence\nin this matter.
We won't let this accusation stand,\nAeleen. Rest easy.
We've gone around to the nearby towns\nand sylvan villages to gather info.
There are other cases where valuable\nmedicinal herbs were picked in the same\nway.

And 'cause of that, the prices of herbs
and medicine made from 'em are out of
control. Some no-good trafficker's the
culprit here, no doubt.
I see. Sarisse, can you mark the sites\nof said unjust harvests on this map?
Got it. Let's see, here...here...and here.
Seems like they're only targeting herbs\nwith a high resale value. And their sphere\nof activity is wide...
Yeah. There's no way a solo act could\ncover that much ground. It's gotta be a\ncoordinated effort.
I think so as well. Especially considering\nthe recent spate of bad weather, which\nwould make woodland traversal difficult.
Poor weather...? Wait, that could be it!\nSarisse, next, please mark the map with\nthe dates when the incidents took place.
Huh? Okay. Um... I think this is about right.\nBut what does that have to do with it?
I knew it! All the nights on which the\nincidents happened were overcast.
Further, all the herb patches were\ndownwind when the thefts occurred.
In other words, the culprits timed their\nefforts around when the wind created\ncloud cover, blocking the moon and stars.
You telling me you remember the weather\nand wind direction for all those days?!\nLike, offhand?!

Of course. I am a guardsman of the
verdure. My people's lives depend on
Mother Nature. I remember about a
month's worth weather at a time.
Now, I think it highly likely that the\nnext crime will happen on a night with\nmany clouds, at an herb patch downwind.
I can predict the weather myself, but if\npossible, I would like to take into account\nthe estimations of others as well.
Melsa's great at forecasts!\nI'll go get her!

Please do. {player_name}, would
you be kind enough to bolster our ranks for
this operation with some of your allies
who possess superlative night vision?
Of course. I'll go call them right away.
Much appreciated. This violation of\nMother Nature shall continue no longer!
Yes. But the culprits are going to target\nthis herb patch, no doubt about it. It ticks\nevery box on the list.
It's gotten pretty late, though. The sky's\nbeen blanketed by clouds for a while now.\nAre these herb-burglars really coming?
We've got our people on lookout all around\nus, so I highly doubt we missed them.
Patience is a virtue when hunting, Luca.
Yeah, yeah.\nHey...wait. Were those footsteps just now?
I heard them as well.\nSomeone approaches!
Our other allies haven't noticed yet.\nAnd I can't line up a clear shot from here.
No. This is more than adequate.
H-hey! Your arrow's never gonna make it!\nYou're just gonna send 'em running for the\nhills!
Who do you think you're talking to? If I\ncouldn't hunt from this paltry distance,\nhow could I call myself a guardsman?
Dammit. Can't believe we'd get caught\nlike this...
You have violated nature's providence.\nSteel yourself for your punishment.
Wait, wait! All we did was come to check\nout some intel we got about this spot!
The sylvan information broker told us\nwe could harvest as many medicinal\nherbs as we wanted, so—
